      <abstract>
        <p>Testimony of Zdeněk and Jiří Steiner, which became part of the Documentation campaign,
          Prague. Brothers were deported from Prague to the Theresienstadt ghetto in September 1943,
          from where they were sent to the so called family camp in Auschwitz-Birkenau. Most of the
          prisoners, who arrived to Auschwitz in this particular transport were murdered half a year
          later, in March 1944. Jiří and Zdeněk Steiner survived due to the fact, that they were
          twin brothers and therefore became subject of Nazi medical experiments in the camp.</p>
      </abstract>

